											<svg width="12" height="12" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><line x1="18" y1="6" x2="6" y2="18"/><line x1="6" y1="6" x2="18" y2="18"/></svg>
										</span>
									</div>
									<div class="p-4 pl-4 sm:pl-3 flex-1">
										<p class="font-bold text-foreground text-xs flex items-center gap-2 sm:hidden">
											<svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="var(--destructive)" stroke-width="2"><line x1="18" y1="6" x2="6" y2="18"/><line x1="6" y1="6" x2="18" y2="18"/></svg>
											Switching strategies too often
										</p>
										<p class="hidden sm:block font-bold text-foreground text-xs mb-1">Switching strategies too often</p>
										<p class="text-xs text-muted-foreground">Jumping between cut, bulk, and maintenance every few weeks prevents any phase from reaching its potential. Each transition requires metabolic adaptation. Commit to a strategy for at least 8-12 weeks before reassessing, unless your circumstances change significantly.</p>
